RT @MarioNawfal 🚨🇺🇸SEN BLACKBURN PRAISES SWIFT ACTION ON BABY FORMULA SHORTAGES

Senator  Blackburn applauded the Department of Health and Human Services for launching Operation Stork Speed, aimed at expanding safe, nutritious infant formula options.

Marsha Blackburn:

"I expressed concerns over the shortages and recalls that the Biden administration failed to address, and am pleased to see Secretary Kennedy taking swift action now!"

The program follows long-standing criticism of the administration’s failure to manage supply issues and recalls. 

Operation Stork Speed promises faster imports, domestic production boosts, and regulatory flexibility to protect American families from future disruptions.

Source: @MarshaBlackburn

RT @TennesseeEMA Severe weather can cause power outages.  Plan for batteries and other alternative power sources to meet your needs if the power goes out, such as a portable charger or power bank.

In the event of an outage:

- Keep freezers and refrigerators closed. 

- Use generators outdoors and at least 20 feet away from building openings. 

- Unplug appliances and electronics to avoid damage from electrical surges. 

- Make a plan for refrigerating medicines and powering medical devices.
